# .trivyignore
#
# List CVE IDs here ONLY when you've deliberately assessed the risk and
# decided to accept it (e.g. a vulnerability in a code path you don't use,
# or one with no available fix yet and low real-world exploitability).
#
# Never add entries here just to make a scan pass - that defeats the point
# of scanning in the first place. Each entry should have a comment explaining
# why it's accepted and by whom, e.g.:
#
# CVE-2023-XXXXX  # Accepted 2026-07-16 by <name> - unused code path, no fix available yet

# --- Debian base image (python:3.12-slim) CVEs with no upstream fix yet ---
# Confirmed via Trivy scan on 2026-07-17: these all show a blank "Fixed
# Version", meaning no patched package version exists yet in Debian's
# repositories. Re-run `apt-get upgrade` (already in the Dockerfile) will
# pick these up automatically once Debian ships a fix - until then,
# `apt-get upgrade` cannot resolve them no matter how often the image is
# rebuilt. None of these packages (util-linux/blkid tooling, gzip, ncurses,
# acl) are directly invoked by the application - they are base-OS utilities
# pulled in transitively, not part of the app's own attack surface.
CVE-2026-53615  # Accepted 2026-07-17 - libblkid/util-linux, no fix available, not used by the app directly
CVE-2026-41992  # Accepted 2026-07-17 - gzip, no fix available, not used by the app directly
CVE-2026-54369  # Accepted 2026-07-17 - libacl1, no fix available, not used by the app directly
CVE-2025-69720   # Accepted 2026-07-17 - ncurses, no fix available, not used by the app directly

# --- perl-base CVEs ---
# perl-base is a transitive dependency of the Debian base image; this
# application never invokes perl. CVE-2026-13221 is rated CRITICAL upstream,
# which is why it's called out separately here rather than bundled above -
# it's accepted specifically because perl is not on this app's attack
# surface, not because the severity is being dismissed.
CVE-2026-13221  # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl-base, CRITICAL upstream but perl is never invoked by this app
CVE-2026-42496   # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl-Archive-Tar, same reasoning as above
CVE-2026-8376    # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl, same reasoning as above
CVE-2026-42497   # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl-Archive-Tar, same reasoning as above
CVE-2026-48962   # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl-IO-Compress, same reasoning as above
CVE-2026-57432   # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl, same reasoning as above
CVE-2026-9538    # Accepted 2026-07-17 - perl-Archive-Tar, same reasoning as above
CVE-2026-57433   # Accepted 2026-07-23 - perl-Storable, CRITICAL upstream but no fix available yet and perl is never invoked by this app (same reasoning as the other perl-base entries above)
